<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chongnyon Leader Condemns Remarks by Ozawa </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1002050294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0438 GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1002050294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, February 8 (KNS-KCNA) [dateline as received] 
-- Paek Han-ki, vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee 
of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan 
(Chongnyon), issued a statement on February 8 denouncing Ichiro 
Ozawa, representative of the Japan Renewal Party, who took issue 
with the DPRK by raising outcries over its "completion of 
nuclear arms development" and "nuclear armament." 
  Condemning Ozawa's outburst as an unpardonable insult and 
challenge to the Korean people, he in the statement said: 
  "We demand that Ozawa immediately withdraw and apologize for 
his grave remarks that insulted the DPRK and the Korean people 
and threatened peace and security on the Korean peninsula. 
  "We hope conscientious politicians including those of the 
ruling party and broad Japanese people will not overlook Ozawa's 
remarks but make efforts to get the Japanese authorities' Korea 
policy rectified. 
  "The Korean citizens in Japan will in the future, too, 
develop friendly relations with the Japanese people on the basis 
of the idea of independence, friendship and peace." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

