<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Paper Says Japan Moving To Become Nuclear Power </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1002044994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0435 GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1002044994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["MINJU CHOSON on Japan's Nuclear Armament Scheme" -- KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, February 10 (KCNA) -- Japan is going to 
put into operation Monju, the first fast breeder reactor, in a 
short time while shipping in large quantities of plutonium from 
other countries. Commenting on this, MINJU CHOSON today 
denounces this as an undisguised move to become a nuclear power 
any moment. 
  The analyst points out: 
  Japan has already developed not only devices and 
technologies 
for the manufacture of nuclear bombs but also long-distance 
nuclear delivery means. The danger of Japan's nuclear armament 
presents itself as a thing of the present-day reality, not of a 
distant future. Japan's nuclear armament poses a grave threat 
to peace and security on the Korean peninsula and in Northeast 
Asia and, further, in the rest of the world. We cannot but 
counter with vigilance the grave situation in which Japan's 
nuclear armament is being promoted in the full-scale stage 
around the Korean peninsula. As we have declared more than 
once, our people who value the dignity and independence of the 
nation as their own life are fully prepared to retaliate on any 
manoeuvrings of the aggressors. 
  If nuclear-free peace and security is to be actually 
guaranteed in Northeast Asia including the Korean peninsula, the 
overall denuclearization of this region must be achieved. For 
this purpose, the people of Asia and the rest of the world 
should pay due attention to Japan's hastened nuclear armament. 
  The denuclearisation of Northeast Asia must be realised 
without fail and it should lead to the total abolition of 
nuclear weapons worldwide. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

