<H3> <TI>   Koreans in Japan Rights Group Writes Kim Il-song </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1002001094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 2221 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1002001094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, February 7 (KNS-KCNA) [dateline as received] 
-- A letter to the great leader Generalisimo Kim Il-song was 
adopted on February 5 at the inaugural meeting of the Human 
Rights Association of Koreans in Japan. 
  The letter says: 
  The inauguration of the association is an epoch-making event 
in guiding the Korean qualified persons and researchers of the 
problem of rights to uphold the great leader Generalissimo Kim 
Il-song and the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il with loyal 
hearts and defend and glorify the socialist homeland of chuche 
centring on the popular masses and to defend and expand the 
rights and life of the compatriots in Japan with their special 
knowledge of law and economics and technique pooled together. 
  The letter says: 
  "You and the dear leader have always wisely led us Koreans 
in 
Japan to defend national dignity and rights as dignified 
overseas citizens of a sovereign state and shown compatriotic 
love and care for us through state policies. So we have won 
legal professions in Japan and conducted legitimate activities 
in special domains. 
  "We will firmly unite the Korean qualified persons and 
researchers around you and the dear leader to actively 
contribute to the prosperity of the socialist homeland of chuche 
and acceleration of the independent and peaceful reunification 
of the country. 
  "And we will strengthen and develop friendship with the 
Japanese people and the world peaceloving people who respect 
human rights and peace and vigorously arouse their support to 
our struggle for defending the rights of the Koreans in Japan." 
  The letter expresses the resolution of the participants of 
the meeting to repay the great love and expectation of the great 
leader and the dear leader with loyalty by fulfilling their 
honorable tasks in a responsible manner with the inauguration of 
the association. 

</TEXT>

