<H3> <TI>   Koreans in Japan Demand End to `Team Spirit' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1002001594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 2234 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1002001594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- MINJOK SIBO, a 
newspaper of Koreans published in Japan, February 1 in an 
article strongly demanded the United States and the South Korean 
authorities officially announce that they would discontinue the 
"Team Spirit" war maneuvers and all other military exercises. 
  Noting with resentment that the United States and the South 
Korean puppet authorities are scheming to hold new large-scale 
military exercises integrating "Ulchi" and "Focus Lens" joint 
military exercises, the paper said this is a grave challenge to 
peace and reconciliation. 
  It warned that if the United States and the South Korean 
authorities continued to cling to war maneuvers, they would be 
held wholly responsible for all consequences arising therefrom. 

</TEXT>

