<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kim Il-song, Kim Chong-il Biographies Praised </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0902235994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1524 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0902235994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- The brief 
biographies of the great leader President Kim Il-song and the 
dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il have evoked lively responses 
worldwide. 
  In 1993 alone, they were reported by newspapers, news 
agencies and radios in scores of countries including India, 
France, Poland, Burundi and Nepal. 
  Foreign publications including the Afghan paper ANIS, the 
Jordanian paper AL CHAAB, the Egyptian paper EL MASSA and the 
Peruvian paper EXPRESO carried the full texts of the brief 
biographies, and radios and televisions of many countries 
including Pakistan, Lebanon, Italy and Nicaragua reported their 
brief biographies at a time drawing a largest number of viewers. 
  Press media said the brief biographies of President Kim 
Il-song and Comrade Kim Chong-il are chronicles of the greatest 
leaders and must books for politicians in the present period. 
  Seminars, lectures, reading, explanatory and other meetings 
on the brief biographies were held by chuche idea study groups 
and organizations for friendship and solidarity in Madagascar, 
Tanzania, Guyana, Uganda and other countries. 
  Last year the brief biographies in nine languages were 
widely 
disseminated among figures of broad strata in some 80 countries 
including the Zimbabwean, Iranian and Burkinabe presidents and 
prime ministers. 
  The Nigerian head of state who is concurrently 
commander-in-chief of Armed Forces and political, public, 
academic and press figures of different countries, upon reading 
the brief biography of President Kim Il-song, highly praised him 
as a great thinker and theoretician who founded the immortal 
chuche idea, as a legendary hero, a distinguished leader of the 
present era and a veteran leader of the international communist 
movement. 
  After reading the brief biography of Comrade Kim Chong-il 
the 
general secretary of the People's Unity Party (Unionist) of 
Jordan and other figures of various countries highly lauded him 
as a great man of the century, a genius of creation and 
construction, the great sun with the noblest human love and 
ever-victorious iron-willed brilliant commander. 

</TEXT>

