<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kim Chong-il's Birthday Celebrated Abroad </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1002002594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 2232 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1002002594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- The birthday of the 
dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il is being celebrated in many 
countries. 
  A celebration meeting was held in Lagos on February 3 under 
the cosponsorship of the Nigeria-the Democratic People's 
Republic of Korea Friendship Association and the Nigerian 
Committee For Supporting the Peaceful Reunification of Korea. 
  Chairman of the Friendship Association, Yemi, Oyeneye, in 
his 
report said that the birth of the dear leader Comrade Kim 
Chong-il, an outstanding thinker and theoretician and a 
tender-hearted teacher of the world's revolutionary people, was 
a great sunrise illuminating the future of Korea. 
  He enjoys deepest respect and reverence not only of the 
Korean people but also of the progressive people of the world 
for the undying exploits he has performed for the human cause of 
independence, the reporter said, and stressed: 
  "The world people highly praise the dear leader Comrade Kim 
Chong-il as the greatest of the great men of the century and the 
sun of mankind." 
  A celebrating meeting was held in Dani Province, Togo, on 
February 1. 
  Korean film shows and photo exhibitions were held at the 
Malagasy parliament, in Lome of Togo, Sikasso of Mali and by the 
Sikasso City committee of the African Party for the Solidarity 
and Justice of Mali. 
  The Zimbabwean paper STAR January 28 carried the gist of 
dear 
Comrade Kim Chong-il's work "Our Socialism Centred on the Masses 
Shall Not Perish" and an article titled "The Korean People Are 
Celebrating the Birthday of Their Leader, Full of 
Self-confidence". 
  His Excellency Kim Chong-il has devoted his all to bringing 
the advantages and vitality of Korean-style socialism into 
fuller play and made an active contribution to strengthening and 
developing the Non-aligned Movement in conformity with the 
demand of the world people fighting for the building of a new 
independent world and promoting friendly and cooperative 
relations with the peoples of all countries, the paper stressed. 
  The Peru-Korea Institute of Culture and Friendship published 
a special issue of its bulletin on January 31. 

</TEXT>

