<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll: Cabinet Support Rate Drops 3.6 Points </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1002125594 Tokyo KYODO in English 1153 GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1002125594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Feb. 10 KYODO -- Popular support for the 
cabinet of Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa has fallen to 59.2 
percent this week from 62.8 percent in December, a KYODO NEWS 
SERVICE poll showed Thursday [10 February]. 
  It was the lowest since Hosokawa formed the coalition 
cabinet 
last August. 
  The KYODO poll, taken Tuesday and Wednesday, also indicated 
that those who do not support the Hosokawa cabinet came to 29.7 
percent, up 5.3 percentage points. 
  Of those polled, 54.5 percent said they opposed the proposed 
"national welfare tax," which Hosokawa presented on February 3. 
The proposal was later revoked. 

</TEXT>

