<H3> <TI>   Hashimoto Concerned Over Hosokawa DPRK Remark </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1402081594 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 13 Feb 94 
Morning Edition p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1402081594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ryutaro Hashimoto, chairman of the Policy Research 
Council of the Liberal Democratic Party, held a news conference 
at the party headquarters on the evening of 12 February. 
Commenting on Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa's remarks on the 
issue of sanctions against the DPRK at the Japan-U.S. summit 
talks that "Japan will take every possible action within the 
framework of the Constitution," Hashimoto criticized the prime 
minister, and said: "We are greatly concerned whether Japan will 
be allowed to take actions within the framework of the 
Constitution in case this issue is turned over to the UN 
Security Council for debate. Since it is not the United States 
but Japan that will be asked to make sensible responses, how can 
the prime minister remain so calm?" Thus, Hashimoto indicated 
his strong concern as to whether the government would be 
sufficiently able to respond quickly to the increasingly tense 
situation in the Far East. 

</TEXT>

