<H3> <TI>   President To Visit Laos, Thailand, SRV, India </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0802195994 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1744 GMT 8 Feb 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0802195994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, February 8 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- At the 
invitation of the Indian President Sh. D. Sharma, the Government 
of the Kingdom of Thailand, the Lao President Nouhak Phoumsavan, 
the chairman of the SRV Le Duc Anh the President of Mongolia P. 
Ochirbat will be on an official visit to India in February 
21-25, the Kingdom of Thailand in February 25-28, the LPDR from 
February 28 up to March 3, the SRV in March 3-6, the Ministry 
for External Relations of Mongolia informed today. 
  The government and people of Laos will welcome President of 
Mongolia P. Ochirbat and those accompanying him during his visit 
to be paid to the Lao People's Democratic Republic considering 
the current visit as an important historical landmark in the 
relationship of the two countries i.e. Laos and Mongolia in the 
period of the transition to market relations. This visit is to 
promote raising of prestige of Mongolia in the South-Eastern 
Asia as a whole region being regarded as a region characterized 
by progressive social and economic development and a political 
stability as well, underlined in connection with the forthcoming 
visit of the Mongolian president to this country. 
  As was said by the Ambassador of Laos to Mongolia Mr. 
Chaleng 
Varinthrasak, the two countries and peoples from time immemorial 
have established traditionally good relations. Mongolia and 
Laos have exchanged visits of their leaders rendering mutual 
assistance and support both in the cause of defence and 
strengthening of their countries and on the international scene. 
The "friendship" hospital and the cattle breeding farm built 
for residents of the Province of Siengkhuang are symbolizing the 
friendly relations of the two countries. At present the 
cooperation in the spheres of economy, trade, and culture should 
be promoted which is nowadays more needed than whenever taking 
into account the possibilities of the two sides being based on 
the principles of equality and mutual benefit, the ambassador 
noted. 
  In late February of the current year the Mongolian president 
is likely to pay official visits to such countries as India, 
Thailand, Laos and Vietnam. 

</TEXT>

