<H3> <TI>   First Non-Buddhist, Non-Moslem Church Approved </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0802200294 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1751 GMT 8 Feb 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0802200294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, February 8 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
Ulaanbaatar city authorities have complied with the request of 
the group of Mongolian and American citizens about foundation of 
a Baptist church in the Mongolian capital. In the rules of the 
Baptist church, which has been presented to the Presidium of the 
City Hural of representatives of citizens, it is pointed out 
that the Baptists of Mongolia would carry out their activity, 
being supported by the International Baptist Organization, carry 
out humane and charity actions, organize a work on teaching 
English language, contribute to development of health 
protection, education, agriculture, sports, radio and television 
broadcasting in the country. 
  Thus, the first non-Buddhist, non-Moslem church in Mongolia 
will be founded. 

