<H3> <TI>   Taiwan Leader on `Vacation;' Meetings Reported </TI></H3>
<H4>   Leader Departs, Ends `Vacation' </H4>
<F P=102> BK1402131694 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 1200 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1402131694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Indonesian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Taiwan President Li Teng-hui left Bali at about 0855 
Central Indonesian Standard Time [0055 GMT] this morning, 
concluding a vacation in Indonesia that began on 9 February. 
President Li Teng-hui left Indonesia for an undisclosed 
destination aboard China Airlines Flight No. B-106. It is not 
yet known whether he will return home or stop in another ASEAN 
country. 
  Reports from Denpasar say that Li Teng-hui and the members 
of 
his delegation -- estimated at 35, including a number of 
ministers -- stayed at the Bali Clear Resort near the Nusa Dua 
tourist resort. 
  There have been no official statements on the Taiwan 
president's activities during his stay in Bali because his visit 
was merely a vacation. In addition, Indonesia has no diplomatic 
relations with Taiwan; it follows a one-China policy. 

</TEXT>

