<H3> <TI>   U.S. Congressmen in Seoul To Discuss Military </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1402115794 Seoul YONHAP in English 1146 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1402115794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, Feb. 14 (YONHAP) -- Six American 
representatives of the House Appropriations Committee flew into 
Seoul on Sunday to discuss the issue of South Korea's share in 
U.S. military expenses in Korea. The Congressmen were led by 
Rep. John P. Murtha, chairman of the Defense Subcommittee of the 
Appropriations Committee. 
  On Monday they conferred with Defense Minister Yi Pyong-tae 
