Sun-yong Tuesday morning before leaving the country on the same 
day aboard a U.S. military plane. Government sources said that 
at their call on Defense Minister Yi, they discussed the 
question of expense share and also the possible deployment of 
Patriot missiles in Korea. The six Congressmen were accompanied 
by five Pentagon officials including a special assistant to the 
Defense Secretary, the sources said. 

