<H3> <TI>   Cuba: Vice President Lage Comments on Embargo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0502025794 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0502025794 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Cuban Vice President Carlos Lage Davila 
described the conversations held with Brazilian President Itamar 
Franco and three ministers of his cabinet as very positive. On 
the third day of his official visit to Brazil, Lage held a press 
conference with more than 20 local and foreign reporters at the 
residence of the Cuban ambassador to Brazil. [passage omitted] 
  When questioned on the lifting of the U.S. embargo on 
Vietnam, the Cuban leader answered that it is the result of the 
Asian country's perseverance in keeping alive their ideals and 
social system. 

</TEXT>

