<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   DA's Aichi, Perry Discuss DPRK Nuclear Issue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1102123194 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 10 Feb 94 
Evening Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1102123194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On the evening of 9 February, Defense Agency 
Director General Kazuo Aichi exchanged views by telephone with 
new U.S. Defense Secretary Perry on the issue of nuclear 
inspections in the DPRK (North Korea). During the telephone 
conversation, they agreed on the need for Japan and the United 
States to communicate and cooperate closely with each other in 
dealing with the issue. 
  Mr. Aichi telephoned Mr. Perry to congratulate him on his 
assumption of office as secretary of defense. According to Mr. 
Aichi, they affirmed that the rough sailing at the Japan-U.S. 
economic framework talks should not impair Japan-U.S. security 
relations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

