<H3> <TI>   Minister Confident of Removal From Watch List </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1502123594 Bangkok Thai Color Television Channel 9 in Thai 
1200 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1502123594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Thai Color Television Channel 9 </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Thai </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The commerce minister expressed confidence that 
Thailand will be removed from the Priority Watch List, or PWL. 
He said this after presenting shields to senior police 
commissioners in recognition of their cooperation with the 
Commerce Ministry in cracking down on video tape piracy. 
Elaborating on Thailand's efforts to rid itself of PWL status, 
Commerce Minister Uthai Phimchaichon said the copyright bill is 
now awaiting the first reading by the House of Representatives 
this year. Thailand has taken measures under the principle of 
international trade and the postponement of the U.S. decision 
made him believe that the United States will remove Thailand 
from the list. 
  [Begin Uthai recording in progress] ...credibility in trade 
and the serious efforts we have made will help convince our 
trade partners like the United States to remove us from PWL. 
Evidently, the United States keeps postponing the announcement 
of its decision on Thailand. This, together with several other 
indications, reflects the growing trust they have in us. They 
are now waiting for more action from us. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

