<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Wants More Insurance Competitiveness </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1502124994 Bangkok KRUNGTHEP THURAKIT in Thai 15 Feb 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> BK1502124994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok KRUNGTHEP THURAKIT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Thai </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Deputy Commerce Minister Chaloemphon Sanitwongchai 
disclosed that the Commerce Ministry and Insurance Department 
have not yet come up with a resolution on the proposal to 
increase the number of insurance companies nationwide. In 
principle, the more companies, the more the people benefit 
because they will have more choices. 
  Chaloemphon said: "The business' present image is not very 
good because certain companies still exploit clients. 
Liberalization will trigger competition and prevent 
maltreatment of clients." 
  The deputy minister, however, reaffirmed that if it is 
decided that more insurance companies will be allowed to 
operate, application screening will be carried out in accordance 
with regulations. He said: "I can assure you that issuing 
permits must be done in a fair manner to all. If not, I will be 
the first to defend the interests of the people." 
  He noted that although liberalization of the insurance 
business to open the door for foreign firms is necessary, 
existing Thai insurance companies need time to improve so they 
will be able to compete with foreign companies. 
  He said: "I believe that Thai companies are not yet ready 
for competition and the government is taking necessary actions 
to defend their business as long as possible. They must make 
efforts to improve and should not only think of relying on 
government assistance." 

</TEXT>

