<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   YONHAP Reports Contact </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1502124094 Seoul YONHAP in English 1232 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1502124094 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Berlin, Feb. 15 (YONHAP) -- North Korea and the 
International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) opened a working-level 
contact on Tuesday on the issue of nuclear inspection of North 
Korea, sources at IAEA said. The sources said North Korea asked 
IAEA on Tuesday morning to have working-level contact. It was 
the first contact between North Korea and IAEA in 20 days after 
their last contact took place on last Jan. 25. 
  Officials of the North Korean Embassy in Vienna carried 
instructions from Pyongyang to the talks, the source said. But, 
no contents of the Pyongyang instructions were immediately 
known. In this connection, IAEA spokesman Hans Meyer said that 
at the moment he could not confirm nor deny the resumption of 
the contact. 

</TEXT>

