<H3> <TI>   DPRK Not To Attend 21 Feb Christian Conference </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1502041394 Seoul HANGYORE SINMUN in Korean 15 Feb 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> SK1502041394 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul HANGYORE SINMUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The North Korean Christian Federation has informed 
its ROK counterpart of its decision not to dispatch a delegation 
to the 43rd general meeting of the ROK Christian Church Council 
which is slated to be opened in Seoul on 21 February, disclosed 
the Christian Church Council on 14 February. 
  The North Korean Christian Federation, in a message sent via 
facsimile on 14 February, said: "The civilian-level exchange 
between the North and South has hit the wall since the South 
Korean authorities, under the pretext of the nuclear issue, held 
off our delegation from attending the funeral service for Rev. 
Mun Ik-hwan," adding, "It is regrettable that we are not able to 
send the delegation to the general meeting." 

</TEXT>

