<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Coalition Opposes Arms Buildup on Peninsula </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1402123194 Seoul YONHAP in English 1153 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1402123194 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pusan, Feb. 14 (YONHAP) -- The Pusan Coalition for 
Democracy and National Unification on Monday called for the 
retraction of an alleged plan of the United States to build up 
arms in South Korea. The coalition with some progressive-minded 
people in the Pusan area as its members, said in a statement the 
United States should retract an "arms buildup plan" forthwith. 
It said that in the buildup plan, the United States seeks to 
deploy Patriot missiles and Apache helicopters in Korea. 
  "The arms buildup plan stands in the way to a peaceful 
resolution of the North Korean nuclear question," said the 
statement. "It is a conspiracy to heighten tension and thereby 
facilitate the sale of weapons whose overseas markets have been 
obliterated by the advent of the de-Cold War age." 
  The coalition also asked the United States to be more 
sincere 
toward nuclear talks with North Korea and called on the South 
Korean Government to turn down the U.S. plan to deploy modern 
weapons in Korea and to resume the suspended inter-Korean 
dialogue. 

</TEXT>

