<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Earmarks $10 Million in Aid to PLO </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1502023694 Seoul THE KOREA TIMES in English 16 Feb 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> SK1502023694 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul THE KOREA TIMES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The government has set aside $10 million to finance 
rehabilitation projects for the Palestine Liberation 
Organization (PLO) in the Gaza Strip and the West Bank city of 
Jericho, government sources said yesterday. The sources said an 
additional $260,000 will be granted for various training 
programs and donation of equipment to the self-rule government 
of Palestinians this year. 
  The financial support will be studied with the PLO side when 
a legitimate recipient body is set up in the autonomous region, 
the sources said. 
  The U.S. Agency for International Development (USAID) agreed 
early this month in Jerusalem to provide $25 million to the 
Palestinian Housing Council to build houses for poor families in 
the village of Jabalia in the Gaza Strip. 
  The sources said the government will consult with the PLO 
over which projects the fund will be financed when the 
Palestinian outlet is formed in the autonomous territory. 
  The $10 million will come from the Economic Development and 
Cooperation Fund (EDCF) which is managed by the government to 
help developing nations. 
  The other $260,000 in aid will be used to train 10 
Palestinians in the manufacturing field here, and to send two 
Korean experts and construction equipment there this year. 
  The sources said that set-up of a legitimate body to receive 
the financial support will be speeded up as Israel and the PLO 
signed an agreement in Cairo last Wednesday on security issues, 
including who will monitor the Palestinian border crossing. 
  The Korean embassy in Jordan has been instructed to closely 
watch the development of Palestinian autonomy in connection with 
the aid program, the sources said. The embassy in Jordan 
handles affairs to the PLO with which Korea has no diplomatic 
relations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

