<H3> <TI>   Opposition Claims President Failed in 1st Year </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1402044094 Seoul YONHAP in English 0420 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1402044094 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, Feb. 14 (YONHAP) -- The main opposition 
Democratic Party [DP] claimed Monday that President Kim 
Yong-sam, who launched a campaign for reform and liquidation of 
authoritarianism a year ago, has run into the wall because his 
policy failed to justify such reform. 
  President Kim's reform has no clear-cut principles and 
targets, said Rep. Kim Pyong-o, chairman of the party's Policy 
Committee, in the DP's evaluation called "the limitations of the 
Kim Yong-sam Administration's reform and 10 acts of misrule." 
  The party listed the following 10 [number as received] types 
of misrule by Kim in the first year of his presidency: 
  Rising consumer prices, failure in the Uruguay Round of 
trade 
negotiations and forced opening of the rice market, negligence 
on the North Korean nuclear issue and a setback in inter-Korean 
dialogue, railroading of bills in the National Assembly, a 
series of man-made disasters, large-scale fraud involving banks, 
setbacks in workers' welfare programs and delay in revising 
labor laws, failure to carry out a pledge to allocate 5 percent 
of Gross National Product (GNP) for education, and personnel 
management based on personal links. 

</TEXT>

