<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Economic Planning Board To Eliminate Positions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1402011794 Seoul YONHAP in English 0057 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1402011794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, Feb. 14 (YONHAP) -- The Economic Planning 
Board will eliminate 17 jobs for grade one through nine 
officials, instead of the originally planned seven positions for 
grade one through four officials, under its downsizing plan. 
  Under the reorganization which will be implemented 
immediately after President Kim gives the go-ahead next week, 
the Economic Information and Education Bureau will be reduced to 
a division responsible for economic information in the Economic 
Planning Bureau. 
  The three bureau chief-level coordinators under the 
assistant 
minister for international policy coordination will be trimmed 
to two, while a new job of defense budget examination will be 
created under the assistant minister for budget. 
  The system of sending a bureau chief-level official to a 
foreign educational institution for study will be scrapped. 
  Several bureau-class offices will be rechristened: For 
instance, the Fair Trade Policy Bureau of the Fair Trade 
Commission will be renamed the Policy Bureau. 
  The reorganization plan will also affect some 20 
division-class offices: For example, in the Economic Planning 
Bureau, the manpower development planning division and the 
social development planning division will be merged into a new 
manpower division. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

